# Module Guide

## Backend Modules

### api/ — HTTP Route Handlers

Each file defines a FastAPI `APIRouter`. All routers are aggregated in `api/__init__.py` under the `/api` prefix.

| File | Prefix | Key Endpoints |
|------|--------|--------------|
| `api_auth.py` | `/auth` | login, refresh, logout, me, permissions |
| `api_hosts.py` | `/hosts` | CRUD, connection test |
| `api_categories.py` | `/categories` | Categories + Systems CRUD |
| `api_scripts.py` | `/scripts` | Script CRUD, versioning, reference files |
| `api_projects.py` | `/projects` | Project CRUD, tasks, access control |
| `api_users.py` | `/users` | User CRUD, role assignment, password reset |
| `api_executions.py` | `/executions` | Results query, SSE execution stream |
| `api_scheduler.py` | `/scheduler` | Job CRUD (one-time, recurring) |
| `api_check_groups.py` | `/check-groups` | Check group CRUD |
| `api_audit.py` | `/audit` | Audit log query (admin) |
| `api_export.py` | `/export` | Excel export of execution results |
| `api_ai.py` | `/ai` | LLM chat integration |
| `api_is_catalog.py` | `/is-catalog` | IS catalog: schema, items, file upload/download |
| `api_ib_profiles.py` | `/ib-profiles` | IB profiles: CRUD, export, apply (SSE) |
| `api_offline.py` | (none) | `/projects/{id}/offline/generate`, `/offline/upload` |

**Pattern for adding a new endpoint:**

```python
from fastapi import APIRouter, Depends
from models.auth_models import User
from services.services_auth import get_current_user, require_permission

router = APIRouter(prefix="/my-feature", tags=["my-feature"])

@router.get("")
async def list_items(current_user: User = Depends(get_current_user)):
    await require_permission(current_user, "my_feature_view")
    # ... logic ...
```

Then register in `api/__init__.py`:
```python
from .api_my_feature import router as my_feature_router
api_router.include_router(my_feature_router)
```

